President Cyril Ramaphosa is addressing the nation on the latest response to the coronavirus pandemic. This comes after the President met with premiers and various religious leaders to try to find a way forward in dealing with the virus. Live stream link below:  In his last address on the pandemic on 28 December 2020, Ramaphosa announced a stricter lockdown after the country experienced an increase in infections due to a new variant of the virus. The adjusted lockdown Level 3 came into effect as a result. 